The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for graphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are both likely categories. The paper also involves graph theory and computational geometry, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another possible category. The use of binary labels and decoding time also suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a potential category. Finally, the paper deals with the specific problem of distance labeling for sparse graphs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
